description: Lists the model packages that have been created.

parameters.name: ModelPackageType
parameters.description: A filter that returns only the model packages of the specified type. This can be one of the following values. UNVERSIONED - List only unversioined models. This is the default value if no ModelPackageType is specified. VERSIONED - List only versioned models. BOTH - List both versioned and unversioned models.

nested_items.name: ModelPackageSummaryList
nested_items.description: An array of ModelPackageSummary objects, each of which lists a model package.

nested_items.name: ModelPackageName
nested_items.description: The name of the model package.

nested_items.name: ModelPackageGroupName
nested_items.description: If the model package is a versioned model, the model group that the versioned model belongs to.

nested_items.name: ModelPackageVersion
nested_items.description: If the model package is a versioned model, the version of the model.

nested_items.name: ModelPackageArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the model package.

nested_items.name: ModelPackageDescription
nested_items.description: A brief description of the model package.

nested_items.name: CreationTime
nested_items.description: A timestamp that shows when the model package was created.

nested_items.name: ModelPackageStatus
nested_items.description: The overall status of the model package.

nested_items.name: ModelApprovalStatus
nested_items.description: The approval status of the model. This can be one of the following values.
PENDING_MANUAL_APPROVAL - The model is waiting for manual approval.

nested_items.name: ModelLifeCycle
nested_items.description: A structure describing the current state of the model in its life cycle.

nested_items.name: Stage
nested_items.description: The current stage in the model life cycle.

nested_items.name: StageStatus
nested_items.description: The current status of a stage in model life cycle.

nested_items.name: NextToken
nested_items.description: If the response is truncated, SageMaker returns this token. To retrieve the next set of model packages, use it in the subsequent request.
